00:10:44.077 --> 00:10:46.580 line:-2 align:center
email-related transparency
and control features.


226
00:10:48.348 --> 00:10:50.050 line:-2 align:center
You may have thought
twice before providing


227
00:10:50.050 --> 00:10:52.286 line:-2 align:center
your email address
to a service before.


228
00:10:52,286 --> 00:10:55,322 line:-2
People who use your app can have
the same apprehension.


229
00:10:55.322 --> 00:10:56.990 line:-2 align:center
They may be worried
that their information will


230
00:10:56,990 --> 00:10:59,092 line:-2
be shared with others
or used to link their purchases


231
00:10:59,092 --> 00:11:01,862 line:-2
or behavior
across apps and websites.


232
00:11:01,862 --> 00:11:04,731 line:-2
In iOS 13,
Sign in With Apple introduced


233
00:11:04.731 --> 00:11:07.167 line:-2 align:center
a new way to sign in
to apps and websites,


234
00:11:07.167 --> 00:11:10.304 line:-2 align:center
allowing people to hide their
names or email addresses.


235
00:11:11,872 --> 00:11:14,541 line:-2
In iOS 15, these benefits
are available everywhere,


236
00:11:14.541 --> 00:11:17.878 line:-2 align:center
using Hide My Email
with iCloud+.


237
00:11:17,878 --> 00:11:20,147 line:-2
From Safari,
where people can easily


238
00:11:20,147 --> 00:11:22,783 line:-2
generate a new email address
when filling in a form,


239
00:11:22,783 --> 00:11:26,186 line:-2
to right in Mail,
while composing a new message.


240
00:11:27.621 --> 00:11:30.257 line:-2 align:center
And these can come in
from other channels.


241
00:11:30,290 --> 00:11:32,292 line:-2
Anywhere you receive
email addresses


242
00:11:32.292 --> 00:11:35.362 line:-2 align:center
might have a Hide My Email
address.


243
00:11:35,362 --> 00:11:37,831 line:-2
When one of your customers
uses Hide My Email,


244
00:11:37.831 --> 00:11:40.701 line:-2 align:center
your email will land
right in their inbox.


245
00:11:40,701 --> 00:11:43,270 line:-2
Make sure to respect their
decision and only request


246
00:11:43.270 --> 00:11:45.606 line:-2 align:center
additional information,
like their name,


247
00:11:45.606 --> 00:11:48.509 line:-1 align:center
if needed for your experience.


248
00:11:48,542 --> 00:11:51,211 line:-2
In order to make email
rich and engaging,


249
00:11:51,211 --> 00:11:54,414 line:-2
emails often contain
remotely-hosted images.


250
00:11:54,414 --> 00:11:57,317 line:-2
When a mail program displays
one of those emails,


251
00:11:57.317 --> 00:12:00.854 line:-2 align:center
remote images are fetched,
revealing when, roughly where,


252
00:12:00.854 --> 00:12:04.691 line:-2 align:center
and on what kind of device
the mail was opened.


253
00:12:04,691 --> 00:12:07,995 line:-2
Many marketing emails now
include unique image URLs


254
00:12:07.995 --> 00:12:10.631 line:-2 align:center
for each user,
or even invisible pixels,


255
00:12:10.631 --> 00:12:13.567 line:-2 align:center
specifically to link
this information to people


256
00:12:13.567 --> 00:12:15.769 line:-1 align:center
when they read their messages.


257
00:12:15.769 --> 00:12:18.605 line:-2 align:center
This resulted in people choosing
between text-only emails


258
00:12:18.605 --> 00:12:21.175 line:-2 align:center
to preserve privacy,
or rendering emails


259
00:12:21.175 --> 00:12:24.411 line:-2 align:center
with full content,
but revealing mail activity.


260
00:12:24.411 --> 00:12:29.049 line:-2 align:center
In iOS 15, we're introducing
Mail Privacy Protection.


261
00:12:29,049 --> 00:12:31,885 line:-2
People can choose to have
iOS privately load


262
00:12:31,885 --> 00:12:35,889 line:-2
remote message content,
hiding their mail activity.


263
00:12:35,889 --> 00:12:38,926 line:-1
This is really cool!


264
00:12:38,926 --> 00:12:41,395 line:-1
And it's great news for you.


265
00:12:41,395 --> 00:12:43,497 line:-2
More people
will read your emails,


266
00:12:43.497 --> 00:12:47.267 line:-2 align:center
with all the images
and visuals you included.


267
00:12:47,267 --> 00:12:49,670 line:-2
If you've been using remote
images to measure the impact


268
00:12:49.670 --> 00:12:53.273 line:-2 align:center
of your campaigns, there are
a few changes to be aware of.


269
00:12:53,273 --> 00:12:56,143 line:-2
Since Mail content may be loaded
automatically after delivery,


270
00:12:56.143 --> 00:12:59.213 line:-2 align:center
the time of Mail viewing
will no longer be correct.


271
00:12:59,213 --> 00:13:01,415 line:-2
And since that content is loaded
without revealing people's


272
00:13:01.415 --> 00:13:04.184 line:-2 align:center
IP addresses and without
detailed headers,


273
00:13:04,184 --> 00:13:06,486 line:-2
the location and type of device
reading the Mail


274
00:13:06.486 --> 00:13:08.555 line:-1 align:center
aren't revealed.


275
00:13:08,555 --> 00:13:10,924 line:-2
And you'll see your
emails as being opened,


276
00:13:10.924 --> 00:13:14.228 line:-2 align:center
regardless of if the user
read it or not.


277
00:13:14.261 --> 00:13:16.730 line:-2 align:center
Next up in transparency
and control,


278
00:13:16,730 --> 00:13:19,299 line:-2
we'll take a quick tour through
focus and indicators.


279
00:13:20,801 --> 00:13:24,805 line:-2
New in iOS 15,
if you have a communication app,


280
00:13:24,805 --> 00:13:27,374 line:-2
you can assist people
in Do Not Disturb


281
00:13:27,374 --> 00:13:29,142 line:-1
or another Focus


282
00:13:29,142 --> 00:13:31,778 line:-2
by requesting access
to read their availability,


283
00:13:31,778 --> 00:13:35,282 line:-2
then sharing that status
within your app's experience.


284
00:13:35,282 --> 00:13:37,718 align:center
To request access to status,


285
00:13:37,718 --> 00:13:40,721 line:0
you'll need
a NSFocusStatusUsageDescription


286
00:13:40,721 --> 00:13:43,123 line:0
key in your app's Info.plist,


287
00:13:43,123 --> 00:13:44,458 align:center
and the User Notifications


288
00:13:44,458 --> 00:13:47,895 line:0
Communication capability
enabled in Xcode.


289
00:13:47,895 --> 00:13:50,964 align:center
For more information on Focus,
check out


290
00:13:50,964 --> 00:13:55,068 line:0
"Send communication and Time
Sensitive notifications."


291
00:13:55,068 --> 00:13:58,672 line:-2
In macOS Monterey,
we've complemented the camera


292
00:13:58.672 --> 00:14:01.508 line:-2 align:center
indicator light
with a recording indicator.


293
00:14:01.508 --> 00:14:03.844 line:-2 align:center
Now, any time
the built in microphone,


294
00:14:03,844 --> 00:14:06,780 line:-2
or W1 or H1 audio device,
is listening,


295
00:14:06.780 --> 00:14:10.784 line:-2 align:center
people can see that with an
orange dot in the status bar.


296
00:14:10.784 --> 00:14:14.087 line:-2 align:center
Of course, part of building
trust is not abusing it.


297
00:14:14,087 --> 00:14:16,456 line:-2
Make sure your app runs
the microphone


298
00:14:16.456 --> 00:14:19.026 line:-2 align:center
only when it makes sense
to people.


299
00:14:19.026 --> 00:14:22.162 line:-2 align:center
As an example,
if your app has a mute button,


300
00:14:22,162 --> 00:14:25,032 line:-2
stop receiving audio from
the system when muted.


301
00:14:25.032 --> 00:14:28.468 line:-2 align:center
Make sure to test your app
on macOS Monterey


302
00:14:28.468 --> 00:14:31.672 line:-2 align:center
to make sure it behaves
the way people will expect.


303
00:14:31.672 --> 00:14:34.074 line:-1 align:center
Also, you can easily confirm


304
00:14:34.074 --> 00:14:36.076 line:-2 align:center
that no third-party
SDKs in your app


305
00:14:36.076 --> 00:14:38.445 line:-1 align:center
are listening unexpectedly.


306
00:14:38,445 --> 00:14:41,081 line:-2
Next, let's look at
tools that provide


307
00:14:41,081 --> 00:14:43,417 line:-2
transparency
for recent app behavior.


308
00:14:44.618 --> 00:14:47.354 line:-2 align:center
App Privacy Report will enable
people to understand


309
00:14:47,354 --> 00:14:49,656 line:-2
what's going on with their
everyday applications


310
00:14:49.656 --> 00:14:53.794 line:-2 align:center
and will be available
in an upcoming software update.


311
00:14:53,794 --> 00:14:56,964 line:-2
It will reveal to people
when your app accesses user data


312
00:14:56.964 --> 00:15:01.034 line:-2 align:center
and sensors, such as Location,
Photos, or Contacts


313
00:15:01.034 --> 00:15:03.504 line:-2 align:center
and show who your app
may be sharing data with


314
00:15:03.504 --> 00:15:05.839 line:-2 align:center
by listing all the domains
your app contacts,


315
00:15:05,839 --> 00:15:08,242 line:-2
as well as the domains
that websites accessed


316
00:15:08,242 --> 00:15:09,710 line:-1
within your app contact.


317
00:15:11,578 --> 00:15:13,814 line:-2
App Privacy Report
will be in Privacy Settings


318
00:15:13.814 --> 00:15:16.517 line:-2 align:center
and can be enabled
by people to better understand


319
00:15:16.517 --> 00:15:18.652 line:-1 align:center
the apps they have installed.


320
00:15:18,652 --> 00:15:20,554 line:-2
If people want to clear usage
history,


321
00:15:20,554 --> 00:15:23,557 line:-2
they can
just turn it back off again.


322
00:15:23.557 --> 00:15:26.293 line:-2 align:center
It's also important to note
that App Privacy Report


323
00:15:26.293 --> 00:15:29.429 line:-2 align:center
will not record ephemeral WebKit
sessions by web browsers,


324
00:15:29.429 --> 00:15:31.832 line:-2 align:center
such as Private Browsing Mode
in Safari.


325
00:15:33.967 --> 00:15:38.172 line:-2 align:center
In iOS 15, Record App Activity
provides export functionality


326
00:15:38,172 --> 00:15:41,408 line:-2
for you to better understand
your apps' behaviors.


327
00:15:41,408 --> 00:15:43,877 line:-2
So, you'll
want to grab the iOS 15 beta


328
00:15:43,877 --> 00:15:46,680 line:-2
and turn on Record App Activity
to get a head start


329
00:15:46.680 --> 00:15:48.682 line:-2 align:center
on what people
will see for your app


330
00:15:48.682 --> 00:15:51.952 line:-2 align:center
in the App Privacy Report
feature.


331
00:15:51.952 --> 00:15:54.555 line:-2 align:center
Then, when you select
Save App Activity,


332
00:15:54,555 --> 00:15:57,758 line:-1
iOS will produce a JSON file.


333
00:15:57,758 --> 00:15:59,860 line:-2
You should review
the content of this JSON file


334
00:15:59.860 --> 00:16:02.663 line:-2 align:center
to confirm your app
behaves as expected.


335
00:16:06.967 --> 00:16:09.203 line:-1 align:center
So, let's take a look.


336
00:16:09.203 --> 00:16:11.371 line:-2 align:center
The JSON will have a list
of stream dictionaries,


337
00:16:11.371 --> 00:16:14.741 line:-2 align:center
one for each time a binary
accessed user data and sensors,


338
00:16:14,741 --> 00:16:17,511 line:-1
like location or camera.


339
00:16:17.511 --> 00:16:20.214 line:-2 align:center
Here's an example
of a single access.


340
00:16:20,214 --> 00:16:23,650 line:-2
First, search for all
instances of the bundle IDs


341
00:16:23,650 --> 00:16:26,353 line:-1
of all your app's binaries.


342
00:16:26.353 --> 00:16:29.122 line:-2 align:center
From there,
the timestamps can help you


343
00:16:29,122 --> 00:16:31,625 line:-2
tie those accesses
to your software behavior.


344
00:16:34.862 --> 00:16:36.997 line:-2 align:center
To see all the domains
you've contacted,


345
00:16:36,997 --> 00:16:39,900 line:-2
look below
the section marker in JSON:


346
00:16:39,900 --> 00:16:41,935 line:-1
there's a final dictionary.


347
00:16:41.935 --> 00:16:46.006 line:-2 align:center
This uses bundle IDs for keys,
so there's one dictionary


348
00:16:46.006 --> 00:16:49.042 line:-2 align:center
for each
of your app's executables.


349
00:16:49.042 --> 00:16:52.312 line:-2 align:center
From there,
you can see all domain contacts,


350
00:16:52,312 --> 00:16:56,383 line:-2
when they were initiated, and if
they were app or user-initiated.


351
00:16:59,186 --> 00:17:00,954 line:-2
Now, let me show you
the difference between


352
00:17:00,954 --> 00:17:04,157 line:-2
a connection by an app
and a connection by a website.


353
00:17:04.157 --> 00:17:06.059 line:-2 align:center
Connections made by
SafariViewController


354
00:17:06,059 --> 00:17:07,928 line:-1
and ASWebAuthenticationSessions


355
00:17:07.928 --> 00:17:11.131 line:-2 align:center
are automatically tagged as
connections by websites.


356
00:17:11.131 --> 00:17:13.133 line:-2 align:center
You can also manually tag
connections


357
00:17:13.133 --> 00:17:15.002 line:-1 align:center
as being caused by a website


358
00:17:15.002 --> 00:17:17.938 line:-2 align:center
if a connection is made
on behalf of third-party content


359
00:17:17,938 --> 00:17:19,940 line:-2
and isn't core
to app functionality.


360
00:17:22,009 --> 00:17:25,412 line:0
At standard layers,
we've added an attribution


361
00:17:25,412 --> 00:17:27,948 align:center
enum to manually tag
a connection.


362
00:17:27,948 --> 00:17:29,850 align:center
You'll need to specify "user."


363
00:17:29,850 --> 00:17:31,418 align:center
If you don't specify,


364
00:17:31,418 --> 00:17:34,188 align:center
connections will be
marked as app traffic.


365
00:17:34,188 --> 00:17:37,257 align:center
This enum exists in
NSMutableURLRequests,


366
00:17:37,257 --> 00:17:40,194 align:center
where you'll want to supply
the MainDocumentURL,


367
00:17:40,194 --> 00:17:42,896 line:0
in NWConnection in the Network
framework,


368
00:17:42,896 --> 00:17:45,098 line:0
and sockets.


369
00:17:45,098 --> 00:17:46,967 line:0
You can also tag connections


370
00:17:46,967 --> 00:17:49,903 align:center
via convenience methods in other
Apple frameworks,


371
00:17:49,903 --> 00:17:53,907 line:0
such as LinkPresentation
and AVFoundation.


372
00:17:53,907 --> 00:17:58,245 line:0
WKWebView has added new methods
to pass an NSURLRequest,


373
00:17:58,245 --> 00:18:00,881 align:center
so you can tag your
connections appropriately.


374
00:18:00,881 --> 00:18:05,485 align:center
For more info, see "Explore
WKWebView additions."


375
00:18:07.387 --> 00:18:09.489 line:-1 align:center
App Privacy Report exists


376
00:18:09,489 --> 00:18:12,759 line:-2
to provide transparency
on app behaviors.


377
00:18:12,759 --> 00:18:15,762 line:-2
And Record App Activity
is a great tool to help you


378
00:18:15.762 --> 00:18:18.565 line:-2 align:center
understand what people
will see when App Privacy Report


379
00:18:18.565 --> 00:18:21.935 line:-2 align:center
becomes available
in an upcoming software update.


380
00:18:21,935 --> 00:18:24,538 line:-2
Your app should access
only data the user would expect


381
00:18:24,538 --> 00:18:26,874 line:-2
and at the times
they would expect.


382
00:18:26,874 --> 00:18:28,075 line:-1
This is another opportunity


383
00:18:28.075 --> 00:18:30.744 line:-2 align:center
to really build trust
with your users,


384
00:18:30,744 --> 00:18:34,414 line:-2
as they can understand more of
what your application does.


385
00:18:34,414 --> 00:18:37,217 line:-2
Also, Record App Activity
is a good way


386
00:18:37.217 --> 00:18:39.653 line:-2 align:center
to better understand
the behavior of the SDKs


387
00:18:39.653 --> 00:18:41.388 line:-1 align:center
you've put in your apps


388
00:18:41.388 --> 00:18:44.424 line:-2 align:center
and confirm their practices
align with yours.


389
00:18:44.424 --> 00:18:47.661 line:-2 align:center
Integrate Record App Activity
into your QA passes,


390
00:18:47.661 --> 00:18:50.831 line:-2 align:center
and confirm that only
the data you expect to access


391
00:18:50,831 --> 00:18:53,567 line:-2
is present
in the App Activity JSON.


392
00:18:54,935 --> 00:18:58,038 line:0
And for our final section
of transparency and control,


393
00:18:58,038 --> 00:18:59,840 align:center
I'd like to walk through
a few existing areas


394
00:18:59,840 --> 00:19:02,142 line:0
where we frequently see
questions from developers.


395
00:19:03.544 --> 00:19:05.612 line:-1 align:center
In late 2020,


396
00:19:05,612 --> 00:19:07,881 line:-2
Privacy Nutrition Labels
went live.


397
00:19:07,881 --> 00:19:09,816 line:-2
Labels are designed
to bring transparency


398
00:19:09.816 --> 00:19:12.052 line:-1 align:center
in a glanceable format.


399
00:19:12,052 --> 00:19:14,388 line:-2
Knowing what your app
will do with their data makes it


400
00:19:14,388 --> 00:19:18,592 line:-2
easier for people to trust you
and engage with your app.


401
00:19:18.592 --> 00:19:21.161 line:-2 align:center
We know how hard building
good privacy is


402
00:19:21.161 --> 00:19:24.431 line:-2 align:center
and that the best work
can be invisible.


403
00:19:24.431 --> 00:19:27.868 line:-2 align:center
Your label is a place you can
show off the hard work you do


404
00:19:27,868 --> 00:19:29,336 line:-1
to protect people.


405
00:19:31,138 --> 00:19:33,807 line:-2
Labels need to be inclusive
of all your practices,


406
00:19:33,807 --> 00:19:37,878 line:-2
all features, and all
OS versions per platform.


407
00:19:37,878 --> 00:19:41,215 line:-2
Labels must line up with your
App Tracking Transparency usage,


408
00:19:41,215 --> 00:19:43,517 line:-2
which brings me
to the next topic.


409
00:19:43,517 --> 00:19:47,988 align:center
App Tracking Transparency
was announced at WWDC 2020


410
00:19:47,988 --> 00:19:53,160 align:center
and was required beginning
in spring 2021 with iOS 14.5.


411
00:19:53,160 --> 00:19:55,362 line:0
Now, people can chose
whether they want to be


412
00:19:55,362 --> 00:19:58,732 align:center
tracked across apps
and websites.


413
00:19:58,732 --> 00:20:00,801 align:center
This lets people more
easily trust new apps,


414
00:20:00,801 --> 00:20:03,437 line:0
and existing ones, too.


415
00:20:03,437 --> 00:20:05,606 align:center
To request permission,
you'll need to provide


416
00:20:05,606 --> 00:20:09,009 line:0
a purpose string explaining
why you want to track.


417
00:20:09,009 --> 00:20:10,544 line:0
You can further explain by
putting


418
00:20:10,544 --> 00:20:13,013 align:center
additional information
ahead of that prompt.


419
00:20:13,013 --> 00:20:14,715 align:center
If you choose to take this
approach,


420
00:20:14,715 --> 00:20:16,950 align:center
there are a few details
to keep in mind.


421
00:20:16,950 --> 00:20:19,620 line:0
For example, you shouldn't
pre-prompt with a yes or no.


422
00:20:19,620 --> 00:20:21,255 line:0
For more information,


423
00:20:21,255 --> 00:20:24,224 line:0
refer to our
Human Interface Guidelines.


424
00:20:24,224 --> 00:20:27,594 line:0
Now, some things to keep
in mind.


425
00:20:27,594 --> 00:20:31,298 align:center
Tracking is about linking user
data across apps and websites


426
00:20:31,298 --> 00:20:34,701 align:center
for advertising purposes
or sharing with data brokers.


427
00:20:34,701 --> 00:20:36,837 line:0
For the detailed definition,


428
00:20:36,837 --> 00:20:39,606 line:0
see the User Privacy
and Data Use page.


429
00:20:39,606 --> 00:20:42,276 line:0
App Tracking Transparency
is about


430
00:20:42,276 --> 00:20:45,579 line:0
more than the IDFA, or
Identifier For Advertising.


431
00:20:45,579 --> 00:20:49,516 line:0
The IDFA is one way to track,
but App Tracking Transparency


432
00:20:49,516 --> 00:20:52,319 line:0
requires you to ask
permission for any tracking.


433
00:20:52,319 --> 00:20:54,488 line:0
As part of your app's
functionality,


434
00:20:54,488 --> 00:20:56,990 align:center
you might collect
names, email addresses,


435
00:20:56,990 --> 00:20:59,426 line:0
or other identifiers.


436
00:20:59,426 --> 00:21:01,428 align:center
Linking data using this
information


437
00:21:01,428 --> 00:21:03,931 align:center
is also considered tracking.


438
00:21:03,931 --> 00:21:06,300 line:0
Fingerprinting,
or the collection


439
00:21:06,300 --> 00:21:08,168 align:center
of multiple bits of
information


440
00:21:08,168 --> 00:21:10,671 align:center
to generate a stable
device identity,


441
00:21:10,671 --> 00:21:13,640 align:center
is disallowed by the developer
program license agreement,


442
00:21:13,640 --> 00:21:15,976 align:center
even if people give you
permission to track.


443
00:21:17,845 --> 00:21:20,280 line:0
If tracking is denied,
all app functionality


444
00:21:20,280 --> 00:21:22,449 align:center
must still be available.


445
00:21:22,449 --> 00:21:25,552 line:0
Make sure that your
App Tracking Transparency usage


446
00:21:25,552 --> 00:21:27,821 line:0
