572
00:27:22,676 --> 00:27:25,479 line:0
and "Boost performance and
security with modern networking"


573
00:27:25,479 --> 00:27:28,916 align:center
videos from WWDC 2020.


574
00:27:28,916 --> 00:27:32,553 align:center
In iOS 15 and macOS Monterey,
we are introducing


575
00:27:32,553 --> 00:27:36,423 align:center
iCloud Private Relay,
a new internet privacy service.


576
00:27:36,423 --> 00:27:39,726 align:center
Included in iCloud+,
Private Relay makes sure


577
00:27:39,726 --> 00:27:42,396 align:center
every internet connection
you make is encrypted,


578
00:27:42,396 --> 00:27:44,965 line:0
and your IP address
no longer identifies you


579
00:27:44,965 --> 00:27:48,702 align:center
or gives away your location
to websites in Safari.


580
00:27:48,702 --> 00:27:51,772 align:center
And the best part, with
Private Relay's unique design,


581
00:27:51,772 --> 00:27:53,540 align:center
no one, including Apple,


582
00:27:53,540 --> 00:27:56,210 align:center
can see both who you are
and which websites you visit.


583
00:27:57,811 --> 00:28:00,047 align:center
Let's briefly explore
how Private Relay works


584
00:28:00,047 --> 00:28:02,683 align:center
when I shop for my new home.


585
00:28:02,683 --> 00:28:05,252 align:center
First, when making a connection
to Furniture Site,


586
00:28:05,252 --> 00:28:08,255 align:center
two different Proxy operators
in the Private Relay Network


587
00:28:08,255 --> 00:28:10,858 align:center
are randomly picked
so that no single operator


588
00:28:10,858 --> 00:28:13,460 align:center
has control or can see
the whole picture.


589
00:28:13,460 --> 00:28:15,996 line:-2
The proxy that accepts
my connection from


590
00:28:15,996 --> 00:28:19,199 line:-2
the internet is called
the Ingress Proxy.


591
00:28:19.199 --> 00:28:21.401 line:-2 align:center
The Ingress Proxy prevents
other servers


592
00:28:21,401 --> 00:28:23,036 line:-1
from seeing my IP address


593
00:28:23,036 --> 00:28:24,872 line:-1
and encrypts my internet traffic


594
00:28:24.872 --> 00:28:26.406 line:-1 align:center
to prevent my network provider


595
00:28:26,406 --> 00:28:28,342 line:-1
from knowing what I'm up to.


596
00:28:28,342 --> 00:28:30,944 line:-2
The relay back
to the internet is provided


597
00:28:30.944 --> 00:28:34.214 line:-2 align:center
by the Egress Proxy,
which prevents the Ingress Proxy


598
00:28:34.214 --> 00:28:36.083 line:-2 align:center
from seeing what website
I'm contacting.


599
00:28:37,184 --> 00:28:39,620 align:center
Private Relay manages
network access in a way


600
00:28:39,620 --> 00:28:42,756 align:center
that doesn't require
identity or account information,


601
00:28:42,756 --> 00:28:45,259 align:center
using RSA Blinded Signatures.


602
00:28:45,259 --> 00:28:47,461 align:center
A cryptographic blinding
operation,


603
00:28:47,461 --> 00:28:49,930 align:center
performed by my device,
lets me redeem it


604
00:28:49,930 --> 00:28:52,432 line:0
for network access,
without giving away


605
00:28:52,432 --> 00:28:55,669 align:center
any information about my account
or who's making the connection.


606
00:28:57,070 --> 00:28:59,239 line:-2
Using the public key
from the Token server,


607
00:28:59,239 --> 00:29:01,375 line:-2
a Private Relay Proxy
can quickly verify


608
00:29:01,375 --> 00:29:02,809 line:-1
network access permission.


609
00:29:04,778 --> 00:29:06,513 align:center
Before making a connection,


610
00:29:06,513 --> 00:29:09,383 align:center
the Private Relay Access Token
Server provides a bundle


611
00:29:09,383 --> 00:29:11,084 line:0
of different tokens to my
device.


612
00:29:11,885 --> 00:29:14,888 line:0
This gives me access to any
proxy operator I choose,


613
00:29:14,888 --> 00:29:16,657 align:center
whenever I need it.


614
00:29:17.758 --> 00:29:19.960 line:-2 align:center
To enforce the separation
of information between


615
00:29:19.960 --> 00:29:22.362 line:-2 align:center
the proxies I picked,
the connection is built


616
00:29:22.362 --> 00:29:24.898 line:-2 align:center
using multiple
layers of encryption.


617
00:29:24.898 --> 00:29:27.000 line:-2 align:center
The proxies
remove layer-by-layer


618
00:29:27,000 --> 00:29:29,670 line:-2
when the connection passes
through.


619
00:29:29.670 --> 00:29:31.939 line:-2 align:center
Only my device
can decrypt every layer,


620
00:29:31.939 --> 00:29:34.641 line:-2 align:center
which is required to know that I
am accessing the Furniture Site.


621
00:29:36,176 --> 00:29:37,544 line:-1
When making the connection,


622
00:29:37.544 --> 00:29:41.048 line:-2 align:center
the Egress Proxy randomly
selects an IP address to use.


623
00:29:41,048 --> 00:29:43,650 line:-2
This helps to prevent linking
my couch search


624
00:29:43,650 --> 00:29:47,120 line:-2
to my lawn mower search,
or my recent table delivery.


625
00:29:47,120 --> 00:29:49,489 line:-2
Over time,
Private Relay connections


626
00:29:49.489 --> 00:29:51.859 line:-2 align:center
are automatically created
and reused


627
00:29:51,859 --> 00:29:54,361 line:-2
to provide IP
address tracking protection


628
00:29:54.361 --> 00:29:57.364 line:-1 align:center
and good performance.


629
00:29:57.364 --> 00:29:59.333 line:-2 align:center
The way Private Relay
hides my IP address


630
00:29:59.333 --> 00:30:01.668 line:-1 align:center
has one more privacy benefit.


631
00:30:01,668 --> 00:30:05,739 line:-2
Since my home IP address can be
geo-coded to my rough location,


632
00:30:05,739 --> 00:30:09,376 line:-2
the Ingress Proxy can share
that location with me.


633
00:30:09,376 --> 00:30:11,411 line:-2
This lets me inform
the Egress Proxy


634
00:30:11.411 --> 00:30:14.314 line:-2 align:center
which group of IP addresses
to choose between.


635
00:30:14.314 --> 00:30:18.285 line:-2 align:center
This is a great example of great
features and great privacy.


636
00:30:18.285 --> 00:30:21.822 line:-2 align:center
Websites can provide
local content in Safari,


637
00:30:21.822 --> 00:30:23.757 line:-2 align:center
while my precise location
stays hidden.


638
00:30:25,692 --> 00:30:27,895 line:-2
Remember, the Ingress Proxy
is the only one


639
00:30:27.928 --> 00:30:30.631 line:-1 align:center
that can see my IP address,


640
00:30:30.664 --> 00:30:33.200 line:-2 align:center
The Ingress Proxy
converts my IP address


641
00:30:33.233 --> 00:30:34.868 line:-1 align:center
to the same IP-based area


642
00:30:34.902 --> 00:30:37.671 line:-2 align:center
that lawnmower site
would have seen,


643
00:30:37.704 --> 00:30:40.207 line:-2 align:center
then returns
an approximated version back.


644
00:30:40,240 --> 00:30:43,076 align:center
In this example,
the Ingress Proxy sends back


645
00:30:43,076 --> 00:30:47,648 line:0
"Bay Area, California," which is
forwarded to the Egress Proxy


646
00:30:47,648 --> 00:30:50,050 align:center
to help it pick from a group
of IP addresses


647
00:30:50,050 --> 00:30:52,953 align:center
that are assigned
to that general area.


648
00:30:52,953 --> 00:30:55,656 align:center
With a regional IP address,
sites that I contact


649
00:30:55,656 --> 00:30:57,591 line:0
can still find nearby stores.


650
00:30:58,458 --> 00:31:00,694 line:0
Let's visualize how this works.


651
00:31:00,694 --> 00:31:03,463 align:center
When I connect,
both sites see connections


652
00:31:03,463 --> 00:31:07,367 line:0
coming from an IP address
that maps to my general area.


653
00:31:07,367 --> 00:31:09,503 align:center
The dots on the map
represent possible


654
00:31:09,503 --> 00:31:11,505 align:center
Private Relay IP address
locations


655
00:31:11,505 --> 00:31:13,574 align:center
that are shared by
everyone in the region.


656
00:31:16.276 --> 00:31:18.478 line:-2 align:center
When the "Use Country
and Time Zone" option


657
00:31:18,478 --> 00:31:21,181 line:-2
is selected in iCloud
Internet Privacy settings,


658
00:31:21.181 --> 00:31:23.550 line:-2 align:center
no hint is provided
to the Egress Proxy.


659
00:31:24,318 --> 00:31:26,420 align:center
So, it picks a random
IP address from the group


660
00:31:26,420 --> 00:31:28,255 align:center
that represents
the much larger region


661
00:31:28,255 --> 00:31:30,791 line:0
that belongs
to the Ingress Proxy.


662
00:31:30.791 --> 00:31:33.093 line:-2 align:center
As a result,
websites will see connections


663
00:31:33,093 --> 00:31:35,929 line:-2
being made
from a broad regional area.


664
00:31:35.929 --> 00:31:39.233 line:-2 align:center
The same set of IP addresses are
used by everyone in the region.


665
00:31:40,300 --> 00:31:42,302 line:-2
With the more generalized
location setting,


